<TITLE> Kosovo independence move would hit security:Russia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 GENEVA, Feb 12 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A unilateral declaration of independence by Kosovo would damage security in Europe, Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov said on Tuesday. Kosovo's independence move has been delayed three times in the past year in deference to Russia's insistence on continuing to search for a compromise and because of its explosive impact on Serbian politics. "It would undermine the basics of security in Europe, it would undermine the basics of the United Nations charter," Lavrov told reporters in Geneva. "A whole number of states, including those in Europe, state that a unilateral declaration of independence is absolutely unavoidable, and they state that they are prepared to support such independence," Lavrov said. "I understand that many fail to realise the most basic things, because we're talking here about the disruption of all the basics and fundamentals of international law in Europe," he said, speaking through an interpreter. The Serbian province's Albanian majority is widely expected to declare independence and gain recognition from Western stat
